(158, 'tk_fb_desc', '<p>Who doesn’t into Facebook nowadays? This feature enables you to market your products through one of the biggest social networking in the world. Reach the highest sales potential with this Facebook integration feature. Don’t worry, we will guide you how to.</p>\r\n                                            <p>How to activate Facebook Apps Integration widget</p>\r\n                                            <ol>\r\n                                                <li><a href=\'https://developers.facebook.com/apps\' target=\'_blank\'><img src=\'http://localhost/dailyhome//wp-content/themes/jastex/admin/images/create-fb-apps.png\' alt=\'create FB Apps\' /></a></li>\r\n                                                <li>Copy and paste your <strong>\'App ID\'</strong> and <strong>\'App Secret\'</strong> into the form.</li>\r\n                                                <li>Choose <strong>\'Page Tab\'</strong>, then fill the <strong>\'Page Tab Name\'</strong> with \'store\' or any name you want.</li>\r\n                                                <li><strong>Save</strong>, then hit refresh button.</li>\r\n                                                <li>Fill in the <strong>\'Page Tab URL\'</strong> with <input type=\'text\' value=\'http://localhost/dailyhome//\' disabled /></li>\r\n                                                <li><a href=\'http://www.facebook.com/pages/create.php\' target=\'_blank\'><img src=\'http://localhost/dailyhome//wp-content/themes/jastex/admin/images/create-fb-pages.png\' alt=\'create FB page\' /></a></li>\r\n                                                <li>Choose your page category, fill the form.</li>\r\n                                                <li><a href=\'http://www.facebook.com/add.php?api_key=&pages\' target=\'_blank\'>Activate it</a> in your Facebook page.</li>\r\n                                                <li><strong>Voila!</strong> Your online store is now integrated with its Facebook fan page.</li>\r\n                                            </ol>', 'yes'),
